<paragraph blockId="2.[139,790,893,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[177,240,894,917]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Notes.</emphasis>
– 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, P. E." box="[265,439,893,918]" firstAuthor="Boissier" journalOrPublisher="Geneve" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1736" refString="Boissier, P. E. (1888). Fl. Orient. Suppl. Geneve." title="Fl. Orient. Suppl." type="book" year="1888">Boissier (1888)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName box="[555,654,894,917]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astartes">
<emphasis box="[555,654,894,917]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">S. astartes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the “Supplementum oF the Flora Orientalis”. He wrote “ 
<taxonomicName box="[683,790,926,949]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astartes">
<emphasis box="[683,790,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">S. astartes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Blanche in litt.)” beFore the Latin description. Ŋe mention oF Blanche as the author “in litt.” by Boissier has been interpreted in different ways in the literature. Floras oF 
<collectingCountry box="[632,732,1021,1045]" name="Lebanon" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
have cited only C.I. Blanche as the author oF the species (sometimes with the mention “in Boiss.”; 
<bibRefCitation author="Post, G. E." box="[468,591,1085,1109]" firstAuthor="Post" journalOrPublisher="Syrian Protestant College, Beirut" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1895" refString="Post, G. E. (1896). Fl. Syria. Syrian Protestant College, Beirut." title="Fl. Syria." type="book" year="1896">Post, 1896</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Post, G. E." box="[602,657,1086,1110]" firstAuthor="Post" journalOrPublisher="American Press, Beirut" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" pagination="1" part="1" refId="ref1915" refString="Post, G. E. (1932). Fl. Syria 1. 2 nd ed. American Press, Beirut." title="Fl. Syria" type="book chapter" year="1932">1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="ThiEbaut, J." firstAuthor="ThiEbaut" journalOrPublisher="Le Caire" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" pagination="1" refId="ref1939" refString="ThiEbaut, J. (1936). Fl. Lib. - Syr. 1. Le Caire." title="Fl. Lib. - Syr." type="book" year="1936">ThiÉbaut, 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mouterde, P. S. J." box="[212,403,1117,1141]" firstAuthor="Mouterde" journalOrPublisher="Edition de l'Imprimerie Catholique, Beyrouth" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" pagination="1" refId="ref1868" refString="Mouterde, P. S. J. (1966). Nouv. Fl. Liban. 1. Edition de l'Imprimerie Catholique, Beyrouth." title="Nouv. Fl. Liban." type="book" year="1966">Mouterde, 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="TohmE, G. &amp; H. TohmE" box="[422,683,1112,1142]" firstAuthor="TohmE" journalOrPublisher="CNRS, Beirut" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1959" refString="TohmE, G. &amp; H. TohmE (2007). Ill. Fl. Lebanon. CNRS, Beirut" title="Ill. Fl. Lebanon" type="book" year="2007">TohmÉ &amp; TohmÉ, 2007</bibRefCitation>
), whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="BouloumoY, L." box="[139,358,1149,1174]" firstAuthor="BouloumoY" journalOrPublisher="Vigot Freres" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1754" refString="BouloumoY, L. (1930). Fl. Liban. Vigot Freres." title="Fl. Liban" type="book" year="1930">BouloumoY (1930)</bibRefCitation>
interpreted the authorship as “Boiss. et B.” [Boiss. &amp; C.I. Blanche].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[139,790,893,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
In the Boissier’s Herbarium oF the “Flora Orientalis” (G-BOIS), 
<emphasis box="[323,446,1245,1269]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Blanche 55</emphasis>
contains a handwritten note by Blanche himselF with a Latin description oF the species (
<figureCitation box="[147,208,1309,1334]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="1.[263,290,1888,1907]" captionTargetBox="[262,1347,279,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[262,1347,279,1870]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. – Lectotype of Silene astartes C. I. Blanche ex Boiss. The morphological description is written by C. I. Blanche at the bottom right of the herbarium sheet. [Blanche 55, G-BOIS]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162048/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). However this description differs considerably From the protologue where Boissier published a new and more complete description by validating the name (
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, P. E." firstAuthor="Boissier" journalOrPublisher="Geneve" page="102" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1736" refString="Boissier, P. E. (1888). Fl. Orient. Suppl. Geneve." title="Fl. Orient. Suppl." type="book" year="1888">Boissier, 1888: 102</bibRefCitation>
). We thereFore ascribe Boissier as the author oF 
<taxonomicName box="[689,789,1406,1429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astartes">
<emphasis box="[689,789,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">S. astartes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W. &amp; H. M. Burdet &amp; G. Long" box="[359,613,1437,1462]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Greuter" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Geneve" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" pagination="1" part="1" refId="ref1797" refString="Greuter, W., H. M. Burdet &amp; G. Long (ed.) (1984). Med-Checklist. A critical inventory of vascular plants of the circum-mediterranean countries. Vol 1. Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Geneve." title="Med-Checklist. A critical inventory of vascular plants of the circum-mediterranean countries" type="book" year="1984">Greuter et al. (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and not as C.I. Blanche as mentioned in the latest flora oF 
<collectingCountry box="[586,681,1469,1493]" name="Lebanon" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
treatment (
<bibRefCitation author="TohmE, G. &amp; H. TohmE" box="[148,412,1496,1526]" firstAuthor="TohmE" journalOrPublisher="CNRS, Beirut" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1959" refString="TohmE, G. &amp; H. TohmE (2007). Ill. Fl. Lebanon. CNRS, Beirut" title="Ill. Fl. Lebanon" type="book" year="2007">TohmÉ &amp; TohmÉ, 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162049/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" targetBox="[827,1477,279,1235]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[827,1207,1252,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[827,891,1252,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Fig. 2. –</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Boiss." authorityName="Boiss." box="[1012,1207,1252,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galataea">
<emphasis box="[1012,1148,1252,1271]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Silene galataea</emphasis>
Boiss.
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis box="[832,997,1277,1297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Sintenis &amp; Rigo 768,</emphasis>
G-BOIS]
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[139,790,893,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, P. E." box="[177,356,1533,1558]" firstAuthor="Boissier" journalOrPublisher="Geneve" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" refId="ref1736" refString="Boissier, P. E. (1888). Fl. Orient. Suppl. Geneve." title="Fl. Orient. Suppl." type="book" year="1888">Boissier (1888)</bibRefCitation>
clearly cited two gatherings in the protologue: “Hab. in 
<collectingCountry box="[331,408,1565,1589]" name="Lebanon" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Libano</collectingCountry>
supra Djebail ad minas AFka (Bl.!)” and “ad Ain SuFar (Peyron!)”. Only 
<emphasis box="[522,634,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Blanche 55</emphasis>
[G00330604] is present in G-BOIS. We Found three duplicates oF the Peyron collection at G and one at P. Each oF them bears the locality “Ain SuFar” and are dated 
<date box="[496,643,1694,1718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" value="1882-06-11">June 11, 1882</date>
. Two oF them have the collection number 1379 mentioned [G00341656, P04987226]) and two [G00341655, G00341657] without any number. All these collections have a glandular-pubescent calyx and match Fully with 
<taxonomicName box="[368,457,1821,1845]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis box="[368,457,1821,1845]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">S. italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Pers. and not with 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astartes">S. astartes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which has a calyx always glabrous. ŊereFore, we choose 
<emphasis box="[139,253,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Blanche 55</emphasis>
housed at G-BOIS as the 
<typeStatus box="[547,646,1885,1909]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">lectotype</typeStatus>
, which is the only material present at G-BOIS and exclude the remaining 
<typeStatus box="[139,230,1950,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">syntypes</typeStatus>
From 
<taxonomicName box="[297,397,1950,1973]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="astartes">
<emphasis box="[297,397,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">S. astartes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
